<TITLE> BDR arrests 1 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chapainawabganj, Apr 05 (bdnews24.com)  Bangladeshi border guards arrested a youth in possession of a pistol in Chapainawabganj Sunday night. The arrested is Shahin Ahmed of Telkupi village under Manakasha Union of Shibganj upazila in the district. Major Nazrul Islam, the operation officer of 39 Rifles Battalion said that he was arrested with a pistol from Bara Tappu village of Shibganj. He told bdnews24.com: "A patrol team caught Shahin red handed at 10pm when he was about to sell the pistol." The BDR operation officer also said that there were two others with Shahin. "But they got away." The border guards handed over Shahin to the Shibganj Police Station filing an arms case against him. bdne
